BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260212T200000Z
DTEND:20260212T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260212T000000Z
SUMMARY:Computer Classes at Main Library 
DESCRIPTION:UNC’s School of Information and Library Science students and 
 Durham County Library have teamed up to provide a series of workshops on 
 computer skills!\n\nThe Community Workshop Series offers basic technology 
 and computer classes. Classes are free to the general public. You can 
 attend all the classes or just the ones on the skills you would like to 
 work on. Stop by for one on one tech help during a drop in tech help 
 session. Computers are provided for use during class or bring your own 
 device!\n\n\n\nThird Floor Computer Lab\n\nMain Library\n\n300 North 
 Roxboro Street \n\nThursdays\n\n3:00 pm - 4:00 pm\n\n\n\nParking is 
 available in the library lot or for free at the North Queen Street Garage 
 which is located at 115 North Queen street which is located directly across 
 the street from the library behind the apartments. Bring your parking 
 ticket to a service point for validation. \n\n\n\nMore questions? Call 
 919-560-9311\n\n \n\nSchedule of Classes\n\nFebruary 12 – Smartphone 
 Basics: iPhone and Android\n\nLearn how to use your smartphone! 
 \n\n\n\n\n\nFebruary 19  – Microsoft Excel Basics\n\nLearn tips and 
 tricks for Microsoft Excel!\n\n\n\nFebruary 26 – Microsoft Word 
 Basics\n\nLearn tips and tricks for Microsoft Word!\n\n\n\nMarch 5 - Drop 
 in Tech Help\n\nOne on one help with a device or computer 
 skill!\n\n\n\nMarch 12 - Cloud Storage Basics\n\nLearn tips and tricks for 
 managing online cloud storage!  \n\n\n\nMarch 19 - Online Scams\n\nLearn 
 how to identify and avoid online scams!\n\n\n\nMarch 26 - Organize Your 
 Digital Files\, Folders and More\n\nLearn tips and trick on organizing your 
 digital files! \n
LOCATION:Computer Lab\, Main Library (300 N. Roxboro St)
ORGANIZER;CN="Megan Koslofsky":MAILTO:mkoslofsky@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Computer Class, Digital/Tech Literacy
UID:LibCal-14288-16218335
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/16218335
END:VEVENT
