SUMMARY:Make It Monday! - Paper Lanterns
DESCRIPTION:Welcome to Make It Monday!\n\nEvery month\, we get together and 
 learn a new craft using equipment from our Express Yourself Room.\n\nThis 
 month\, we are creating paper lanterns!\n\nFebruary 17 is Chinese Lunar New 
 Year\, the start of the next year in the lunar calendar. This year is the 
 Year of the Horse.\n\nWe'll walk you through how to use the Cricut Maker to 
 make beautiful lanterns to celebrate the Lunar New Year!\n\n 
 \n\nREGISTRATION IS REQUIRED. SPACE IS LIMITED.\n\nRecommended for AGES 7 - 
 14 | This craft is difficult for younger children.\n\nPlease be on time to 
 guarantee your supplies.\n\n
LOCATION:South Regional - Children's Programming Room\, South Regional Library (4505 S. Alston Ave)
ORGANIZER;CN="Amaris Torres":MAILTO:amaristorres@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Arts & Crafts, Digital/Tech Literacy, Social, STEAM
