SUMMARY:Adult Story Time -- Kafkaesque Tales
DESCRIPTION:Read-alouds are for grown-ups too! Join us for a weekday 
 evening adult story time at the North Regional Library. Flop on the carpet 
 with a floor pillow\, pull up a chair\, or sit at a table if you want to 
 bring your own dinner or snacks. Spend an hour listening to read-alouds 
 from books and stories in the library collection. Tea\, coffee\, and hot 
 chocolate will be provided.\n\nThis month: Stories in the style of 
 Kafka.\n\nWhat happens when some of the most original literary minds of 
 today take an idea\, a mood\, or a line from the work of Kafka and use it 
 to spark something new? From the anthology\, a cage went in search of a 
 bird\, we'll read stories by Elif Batuman and Yiyun Li.\n\nRegistration is 
 appreciated but not required.\n\nE-mail Bob with any questions: 
 rskesler@dconc.gov
LOCATION:North Regional - Children's Programming Room\, North Regional Library (221 Milton Rd)
ORGANIZER;CN="Bob S.":MAILTO:rskesler@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Story Time
