SUMMARY:MS Self-Help Group
DESCRIPTION:\n\nThis group offers peer-led support to share experiences and 
 knowledge on various aspects of living and coping with MS.\nAll are 
 welcome\, especially those affected by Multiple Sclerosis.\n\nThe group 
 will meet monthly at North Regional Library on the third Tuesday\, 
 January-June and September-November. Attendees can join the meeting in 
 person at the library\, or via Zoom. Be sure to register to get the Zoom 
 link. Registration is not necessary to come in person.\n\nFor more 
 information:\n\nContact Sol Sanders at (312) 975-7382/*iMessage\, 
 solange.sanders@gmail.com\,\n\nBirdie Almodovar at (919) 
 525-4475/almodovarm1979@gmail.com\, or\n\nMS Navigator at 1-(800) 344-4867 
 or www.nationalmssociety.org/msnavigator\n\n
LOCATION:North Regional - Children's Programming Room\, North Regional Library (221 Milton Rd)
ORGANIZER;CN="Emily Tobias":MAILTO:etobias@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Announcements, Health & Fitness
