SUMMARY:Testers & Tasters Cookbook Club
DESCRIPTION:\n\nTesters & Tasters Cookbook Club is a place to talk about 
 food and cooking!\n\nCome share your experiments\, experiences\, triumphs\, 
 and tragedies.\n\nThis month's theme: Finger Foods Only!\n\nOur February 
 meeting will be a no-utensil zone as we focus on canapés\, appetizers\, 
 hors d'oeuvres\, and all those other tasty bites that you can eat with just 
 your fingers (exception: toothpicks and skewers are acceptable). Savory or 
 sweet\, warm or cold.\n\nThere will be several cookbooks available for 
 browsing at the North Regional Library information desk\, but you can get 
 your recipe from any cookbook or other source.\n\nWhen you know the name of 
 the dish you'll be bringing\, please email the name and source to 
 etobias@dconc.gov.\n\nAnd don't forget some containers for 
 leftovers!\n\nQuestions? Email etobias@dconc.gov or call 
 919-560-0140.\n\nRegistration closes 24 hours before the meeting\, but 
 email me if you've missed the deadline and still want to come.\n\nHappy 
 Cooking to all!\n\n \n\nAll in-person programming is subject to change or 
 cancellation based on current COVID conditions.\n\n
LOCATION:North Regional - Children's Programming Room\, North Regional Library (221 Milton Rd)
ORGANIZER;CN="Emily Tobias":MAILTO:etobias@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Book Club, Food & Cooking
UID:LibCal-14288-15946876
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/15946876
END:VEVENT
