BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260218T230000Z
DTEND:20260219T003000Z
DTSTAMP:20260218T000000Z
SUMMARY:House Shopping with Home Repair Lab: What to Look For Before You Buy
DESCRIPTION:Want help sifting through the massive amounts of information 
 out there about buying a home?\nJoin Chris and Mindy Meyers from Home 
 Repair Lab to learn about what to look for when buying a home! This 
 lecture-focused class will help you learn more about your role as a buyer\, 
 and what you can look for as a buyer or a renter. Relevant for homeowners 
 and first time home buyers. Renters may find part of this information 
 particularly useful\, and the rest more geared towards buyers. The first 
 hour will be lecture\, followed by Q&A.\n\nFurther class 
 description:\n\nLearn about where to find useful information about a home 
 before you visit in person. We'll show how and where to find structural\, 
 land\, and tax information to significantly reduce your information 
 disadvantage as a buyer. We will also demonstrate how and what to "inspect" 
 around and on site and point out common "red" flags. Finally\, we'll 
 reconcile everything into making more confident decisions when buying or 
 walking away from a property.\n\nIf you have any accessibility questions or 
 accommodation needs\, please contact us at Maker_STEAM@dconc.gov. We ask 
 that all requests be made at least 3 business days prior to the event to 
 ensure we can provide the best accommodations possible.
LOCATION:Conference Room #3214\, Main Library (300 N. Roxboro St)
ORGANIZER;CN="Caroline Flory":MAILTO:cflory@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Accommodations Available, Sensory Friendly, STEAM
UID:LibCal-14288-15947129
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/15947129
END:VEVENT
