SUMMARY:Open Office Hours with City-County Planning Staff / Horarios de Oficina Abierta con el Personal de Planificación de la Ciudad y el Condado
DESCRIPTION:The City-County Planning Department is updating the Unified 
 Development Ordinance (UDO)! The UDO sets the rules for how land is 
 developed in Durham\, and they want your input!\n\nThey will host recurring 
 office hours throughout the project on:\n\n\n	First Thursdays 3p-6p\n	Third 
 Thursdays 10a-1p\n\n\nDrop in with your questions and input!\n\n\n¡El 
 Departamento de Planificación de la Ciudad y el Condado ésta actualizando 
 la Ordinanza Unificada de Desarrollo (UDO)! ¡La UDO establece las reglas 
 sobre cómo se desarrollo a tierra en Durham\, y qieremos su 
 opinión!\n\nTendremos horarios de oficina recurrentes durante todo el 
 proyecto. \n\n\n	Los Primeros Jueves  3p-6p\n	Los Terceros Jueves 
 10a-1p\n\n\n¡Trae tus preguntas y aportes!
LOCATION:Main Library - Café area - 2nd floor\, Main Library (300 N. Roxboro St)
ORGANIZER;CN="Jana Bradley":MAILTO:jbradley@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Business, Community Engagement, Durham
UID:LibCal-14288-16200080
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/16200080
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260219T150000Z
DTEND:20260219T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260219T000000Z
SUMMARY:This Week In the Lab: Paper Crafts
DESCRIPTION:Join the STEAM Team in the Innovation Lab during specified open 
 hours to do paper crafts by creating your own Zine and fold 
 origami!\n\nZines (pronounced "zeens") are tough to define because they can 
 be so many things! Basically\, they are self-published\nbooklets containing 
 anything you want - art\, writing\, drawings\, recipes\, poetry\, comics\, 
 etc. The content and look\nare totally up to the creator. It's all about 
 self-expression. Origami is an ancient art technique to fold paper into 
 exciting and unexpected shapes.\n\nThis is a self-paced activity. You can 
 drop in during the listed Open Lab Hours.\n\nInnovation Lab Open 
 Hours:\n\nMonday: Closed\nTuesday: 1pm - 3pm (*different this 
 week)\nWednesday: 3pm - 7pm\nThursday: 10am - 2pm\nFriday: 1pm - 
 5pm\nSaturday: 11am - 1pm and 3pm - 5pm\n\nHours subject to change based on 
 staffing and programming needs.
LOCATION:Main Library (300 N. Roxboro St)
ORGANIZER;CN="Caroline Flory":MAILTO:cflory@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Arts & Crafts, Maker, STEAM
UID:LibCal-14288-16025502
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/16025502
END:VEVENT
