SUMMARY:Reading Time with Ms. Chloe
DESCRIPTION:Registration Required. To schedule a time\, go to: Make an 
 Appointment - DCoL Events & Room Reservations - Durham County 
 Library\n\nDoes your child need more reading practice and could benefit 
 from more reading aloud time? Or are they just learning phonics sounds and 
 need more practice to build blending skills? Then this program is for them! 
 Schedule a 20-minute session for your child with Ms. Chloe to work together 
 with your child on reading and blending practice. You’re welcome to bring 
 your own book or I’ll pull some books that will work for their range. 
 \n\nWhile parents/ guardians don’t have to attend\, they must remain on 
 the children’s floor while their child is attending their session.\n\nFor 
 more information\, contact: chloebullock@dconc.gov
LOCATION:Main Library - Children's Area\, Main Library (300 N. Roxboro St)
ORGANIZER;CN="Chloe Bullock":MAILTO:chloebullock@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:
