SUMMARY:Ink & Inspiration: Jacci Gresham
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a fun Storytime celebrating Jacci Gresham\, the 
 first known Black female tattoo artist and a true art trailblazer! We’ll 
 read her book Make Your Mark and learn how she used creativity and courage 
 to follow her dreams. Then kids will become artists themselves by designing 
 and giving “tattoos” using safe\, temporary materials. A colorful 
 celebration of art\, history\, and self-expression—come make your mark! 
 Registration is required! \n\nIf you have any accessibility questions or 
 accommodation needs\, please contact us at cromero@dconc.gov. We ask that 
 all requests be made at least three (3) business days prior to the event to 
 ensure we can provide the best accommodations possible! All ages are 
 welcome!
LOCATION:North Regional - Children's Programming Room\, North Regional Library (221 Milton Rd)
ORGANIZER;CN="Chelsea Romero":MAILTO:cromero@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:
