DTEND:20260220T223000Z
DTSTAMP:20260220T000000Z
SUMMARY:Muddy Buddies: The Story of North Carolina Crayfish
DESCRIPTION:Crawfish? Crawdads? Mudbugs? Ever encountered one of these 
 freshwater crustaceans in your backyard and wondered what they are all 
 about? Come meet a crayfish or two and learn about these amazing creatures 
 and the essential role they play in the biodiversity of North Carolina! Q&A 
 to follow! All ages welcome!\n\nThis program will be presented by Devin 
 Raburn. Devin is a Graduate Student at North Carolina State University's 
 Department of Applied Ecology. She is also the Graduate Research Assistant 
 for the NC Cooperative Fish and Wildlife Research Unit.
LOCATION:Southwest Meeting Room\, Southwest Regional Library (3605 Shannon Rd)
ORGANIZER;CN="Raivynn Smith":MAILTO:raivynnsmith@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Accommodations Available, Classes & Lectures, Environmental, High Sensory Stimulation, Other, STEAM
