SUMMARY:South TGNBC - February Meeting
DESCRIPTION:Welcome to the South Tween Graphic Novel Book Club 
 (TGNBC)!\n\nEvery month\, the South TGNBC will explore a different genre 
 through reading\, discussion\, a themed snack\, and an activity. \n\nTwo 
 graphic novels will be chosen for each month\, and members can pick one or 
 both to read. Books are available for those who have library cards to pick 
 up at South Regional Library during business hours every day leading up to 
 the meeting. Members must be age 8 - 13 (email amaristorres@dconc.gov to 
 request an exception). An online version may be coming soon\, if there is 
 enough demand.\n\nThe month of February we will be exploring the Romance 
 genre with these graphic novels:\n\n- Cross my Heart and Never Lie by Nora 
 Dasnes\n\n- Crush by Svetlana Chmakova\n\n- Bonus: A first Time for 
 Everything by Dan Santat
LOCATION:South Regional - Children's Programming Room\, South Regional Library (4505 S. Alston Ave)
ORGANIZER;CN="Amaris Torres":MAILTO:amaristorres@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Book Club, Literacy, Social
UID:LibCal-14288-15953085
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/calendar/14288/SouthTGNBC
END:VEVENT
