SUMMARY:Computer Classes: Drop-In Tech Help
DESCRIPTION:Need help outside of a class? Want some 1:1 time to figure out 
 your tech? Join us for drop in tech help! We will have instructors from the 
 Community Workshop Series at UNC-CH ready to assist you. Registration 
 strongly encouraged!\n\nThings we can help with:\n\n\n	Using library 
 e-resources (Libby\, Hoopla\, Consumer Reports\, etc)\n	Setting up an email 
 or online account\n	Help filling out an online application\n	Help with 
 using applications like Word\, Excel\, and Google Apps\n\n\nWe cannot help 
 with resume creation. Additionally\, we cannot offer medical\, financial or 
 legal advice. If you need in-depth assistance with job seeking\, we can 
 refer you to Business Services. \n\nThis class is a part of a series of 
 computer classes. See the schedule below:\n\nMonday\, February 16: Excel 
 Basics\nMonday\, February 23: Drop-In Tech Help\nMonday\, March 2: 
 PowerPoint Basics \nMonday\, March 9: Drop-in Tech Help\nMonday\, March 23: 
 Organize Your Photos\, Files\, & More\nMonday\, March 30: Drop-in Tech 
 Help\nMonday\, April 6: AI Basics
LOCATION:Southwest Meeting Room\, Southwest Regional Library (3605 Shannon Rd)
ORGANIZER;CN="Raivynn Smith":MAILTO:raivynnsmith@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Computer Class, Digital/Tech Literacy
UID:LibCal-14288-16198857
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/16198857
END:VEVENT
