SUMMARY:Dental Hygiene Storytime
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a Dental Hygiene Storytime at Southwest Regional 
 Library! Hosted by Tyler Baity\, we will read books together and engage in 
 a hands-on activity\; kids will be guided through proper brushing and 
 flossing techniques in a fun\, interactive way\, while reinforcing healthy 
 daily habits!\n\nTyler Baity is a prospective dental student passionate 
 about improving oral health access and education within the community. He 
 previously founded a campus organization at UNC that raised funds to 
 provide "smile kits" filled with essential dental hygiene products to 
 individuals in underserved areas. Tyler enjoys working with children and is 
 committed to helping young learners build strong\, healthy habits that last 
 a lifetime.
LOCATION:Southwest Regional - Children's Programming Room\, Southwest Regional Library (3605 Shannon Rd)
ORGANIZER;CN="Kristen Stockdale":MAILTO:kstockdale@dconc.gov
