BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260225T230000Z
DTEND:20260226T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260225T000000Z
SUMMARY:Business Book Club - The 5 Types of Wealth
DESCRIPTION:Do you have an interest in non-fiction books about business\, 
 finance\, economics\, or career development? Do you enjoy thoughtful 
 discussions with fellow entrepreneurs? Sign up for our Business Book Club 
 meeting! This month\, we'll be discussing "The 5 Types of Wealth" by Sahil 
 Bloom.\n\nThroughout your life\, you’ve been slowly indoctrinated to 
 believe that money is the only type of wealth. In reality\, your wealthy 
 life may involve money\, but in the end\, it will be defined by everything 
 else.\n\nAfter three years of research\, personal experimentation\, and 
 thousands of interviews across the globe\, Sahil Bloom has created a 
 groundbreaking blueprint to build your life around five types of wealth: 
 Time Wealth\, Social Wealth\, Mental Wealth\, Physical Wealth\, and 
 Financial Wealth. A life of true fulfillment engages all five types\, 
 working dynamically and in concert across the seasons of your 
 journey.\n\nThrough powerful storytelling\, science-backed practices\, and 
 actionable insights\, in The 5 Types of Wealth\, you’ll learn:\n\n How to 
 prioritize energy-creating tasks to unlock more time in your day\n How to 
 create deeper bonds and build a powerful network\n How to engage your 
 purpose to spark continuous growth\n How to maximize health and vitality 
 through three simple principles\n How to achieve financial independence and 
 define your version of “enough”\n\nWhether you are a recent graduate\, 
 new parent\, midlife warrior\, retiree\, or anything in between\, The 5 
 Types of Wealth will help you act on your priorities to create an instant 
 positive impact in your daily life\, make better decisions\, and design the 
 life you’ve always dreamed of.\n\n \n\nBring your questions\, 
 observations\, and reflections!
LOCATION:Meeting Room #4347\, Main Library (300 N. Roxboro St)
ORGANIZER;CN="Austin Daniels":MAILTO:ausdaniels@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Book Club, Business, Career Development
UID:LibCal-14288-15888740
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/15888740
END:VEVENT
