SUMMARY:Read & Sip
DESCRIPTION:Are you looking for the community of a book club without the 
 commitment? Do you want to get more reading done\, but you struggle to find 
 the time and stay focused? Grab your book and come to our Read & 
 Sip!\n\nGrab a warm beverage\, listen to some music\, and read your book in 
 the company of other avid readers. At the end\, we will come together to 
 share what we have been spending our time reading.\n\nWe will spend 45 
 minutes reading our books\, and then the final 15 minutes will be dedicated 
 to group discussion.\n\nRegistration is appreciated\, but not 
 required.\n\nQuestions? Contact Mara (she/her): mplantholt@dconc.gov
LOCATION:East Regional - Children's Programming Room\, East Regional Library (211 Lick Creek Lane)
ORGANIZER;CN="Mara Plantholt":MAILTO:mplantholt@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Book Club
