BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260225T230000Z
DTEND:20260226T003000Z
DTSTAMP:20260225T000000Z
SUMMARY:Colorful Reads Book Club
DESCRIPTION:Love reading stories from diverse authors? Do you find yourself 
 seeking out books with a diverse array of characters and experiences? Join 
 the Colorful Reads Book Club\, where we will read different fiction books 
 every month that are from diverse authors and feature characters with 
 varied identities\, orientations\, and backgrounds. New members are always 
 welcome! Light refreshments will be provided!\n\nThis month we are reading 
 Hitting a Straight Lick With a Crooked Stick by Zora Neale Hurston (also 
 available as an e-book and e-audiobook)\n\nHave questions about book club? 
 Wanna pass along book suggestions? Email Raivynn at 
 raivynnsmith@dconc.gov.\n\nIf you have questions about accessibility\, 
 program stimulation levels\, and/or need disability accommodations\, please 
 contact us at 919-560-8596.
LOCATION:Southwest Regional - Children's Programming Room\, Southwest Regional Library (3605 Shannon Rd)
ORGANIZER;CN="Raivynn Smith":MAILTO:raivynnsmith@dconc.gov
