BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260226T210000Z
DTEND:20260226T220000Z
DTSTAMP:20260226T000000Z
SUMMARY:Laser Cut Your Own Acrylic Earrings
DESCRIPTION:Join the Maker   STEAM team to use the laser cutter to cut and 
 engrave acrylic earrings in a small group learning environment with 
 hands-on help! We will use our materials and provide materials for one pair 
 of acrylic earrings per registrant. Come ready with a design idea\, a .jpg 
 or .png of your design image\, or just curiosity and we will have a few 
 templates to choose from as well.\n\nThis small-group atmosphere will help 
 introduce you to the laser cutter in a welcoming setting and show you the 
 process of completing a laser cut project to help you prepare for when you 
 reserve the laser cutter on your own in the future.\n\nRegistration is 
 required. Participants will need to sign a safety waiver when in the 
 makerspace. (This program is open to teens and adults. Teens under the age 
 of 18 must have a guardian/parent present to sign the waiver.)\n\nWe also 
 ask that you take the online\, self-paced laser cutter orientation prior to 
 coming to the program (if you haven't already) so that the orientation 
 setup steps are completed.\n\nNote: If you have any accessibility questions 
 or accommodation needs\, please contact us at Maker_STEAM@dconc.gov. We ask 
 that all requests be made at least 3 business days prior to the event to 
 ensure we can provide the best accommodations possible!
LOCATION:Innovation Lab\, Main Library (300 N. Roxboro St)
ORGANIZER;CN="Caroline Flory":MAILTO:cflory@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:High & Low Sensory Stimulation, Innovation Lab, Maker, STEAM
UID:LibCal-14288-16162021
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/16162021
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260226T210000Z
DTEND:20260226T220000Z
DTSTAMP:20260226T000000Z
SUMMARY:Read to a dog @ Southwest!
DESCRIPTION:Relax and read with a dog! This program brings dogs and 
 reluctant readers together for 15 minutes of companionship. Handlers and 
 their dogs provide quiet encouragement to children so that they might 
 develop a love of reading and improve communication skills. Canines for 
 Literacy is an affiliate program of Reading Education Assistance Dogs® 
 (READ®).\n\nNEW IN 2026: Starting in the new year\, we will be hosting TWO 
 therapy teams during this event\, which means double the number of sign up 
 slots! Each therapy team will consist of one dog and one handler\, and will 
 be able to host one reader at a time. We've denoted them by Therapy Team #1 
 and Therapy Team #2 in the sign up link.\n\nUse this link to sign up for 
 one 15-minute time slot.\n\nPlease feel free to bring a few books of your 
 choice to read! When your time slot is about to begin\, please hang out 
 outside the door of the Children's Programming Room and someone will let 
 you in when it is your time to read! Thanks :)\n\nIf you have questions 
 about accessibility\, program stimulation levels\, and/or need disability 
 accommodations\, please contact us at (919) 560-8592.
LOCATION:Southwest Regional - Children's Programming Room\, Southwest Regional Library (3605 Shannon Rd)
ORGANIZER;CN="Abbie Westphalen":MAILTO:awestphalen@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Literacy
UID:LibCal-14288-15314675
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/15314675
END:VEVENT
