BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260226T211500Z
DTEND:20260226T223000Z
DTSTAMP:20260226T000000Z
SUMMARY:Beginner Sewing Machine Tutorial
DESCRIPTION:Join us in Express Yourself for a basic sewing machine 
 tutorial. You will learn the parts of a sewing machine\, how to wind a 
 bobbin\, how to thread the sewing machine\, choose a stitch\, and sew a 
 straight line. This tutorial is designed for absolute beginners. All 
 materials will be provided. Please do not bring your own sewing projects to 
 this tutorial. Questions? Contact Jessica at jllundin@dconc.gov. Open to 
 both adults and teens. \n\nExpress Yourself is made possible through the 
 generosity of the Durham Library Foundation.
LOCATION:Express Yourself / Study Room 3\, South Regional Library (4505 S. Alston Ave)
ORGANIZER;CN="Jessica Lundin":MAILTO:jllundin@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Arts & Crafts, Durham Library Foundation, Express Yourself, Maker, Other
UID:LibCal-14288-16233482
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/16233482
END:VEVENT
