SUMMARY:Pokémon Day: Cards and Clay Creations!
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate Pokémon Day at North Regional Library!\n\nKids are 
 invited to bring their Pokémon cards to show off their collections\, talk 
 strategy with fellow Trainers\, and trade* cards if they choose. 
 Participants can also use foam air-dry clay to sculpt Poké Balls or 
 Pokémon-inspired characters. \n\n*Trading is optional and participant-led 
 with parental/caregiver supervision. The Library does not mediate trades\, 
 so please trade responsibly.\n\nPlease email Lauren at lwise@dconc.gov.  
 Thank you!
