SUMMARY:Duke Ballet and Books
DESCRIPTION:Ballet & Books is a national nonprofit organization striving to 
 reduce the literacy gap through the paired storytelling of dance and 
 reading.  \n\nFor ages 6-9 years old. This is program is for children's 
 ages 6-9 years. It includes a ballet class\, and a reading and writing 
 mentorship on Saturdays from 12:00 pm-1:30 pm beginning January 
 24.\n\nEmail duke@balletandbooks.org to register or for additional 
 information.
LOCATION:Main Library (300 N. Roxboro St)
ORGANIZER;CN="Main Library":MAILTO:main@durhamcountylibrary.org
