BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260228T190000Z
DTEND:20260228T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260228T000000Z
SUMMARY:Mallarmé Music: Forgotten Clefs: Renaissance Wind Instruments
DESCRIPTION:Introducing the current and next generation to Renaissance 
 music\, Forgotten Clefs\, the Renaissance wind ensemble\, presents a FREE 
 family-friendly concert. Learn about the instruments that were the 
 forerunners of today’s oboes\, flutes and bassoons including the shawm\, 
 recorder and dulcian. Hear the music that was written for these instruments 
 over 500 years ago!\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n \n\nFamily concerts are about an 
 hour long and are appropriate for folks 5 years and older\, held at the 
 Main Branch of the Durham County Library. FREE and open to the public. More 
 info 
 https://www.mallarmemusic.org/event/family-concert-renaissance-tunes-with-forgotten-clefs/ 
 \n\n \n\nSponsored by Mark and Cindy Kuhn\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n
LOCATION:Main Children's Programming Room\, Main Library (300 N. Roxboro St)
ORGANIZER;CN="Chloe Bullock":MAILTO:chloebullock@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Humanities, Music, Sensory Friendly
UID:LibCal-14288-14817787
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/14817787
END:VEVENT
