BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260228T210000Z
DTEND:20260228T220000Z
DTSTAMP:20260228T000000Z
SUMMARY:Books & Brushes
DESCRIPTION:Enjoy reading and discussing one of the bestselling Young Adult 
 novels.  Full of twists and delicious secrets\, this is a read to enjoy!  
 This is a Young Adult book club recommended for teens ages 14 to 18 and new 
 adults 18-24 to read\, discuss\, and paint as we talk about what we like\, 
 love\, and hate about our books.\n\nThis month\, we are reading THE 
 MAGICIAN by Michael Scott.  Synopsis: After fleeing Ojai\, Nicholas\, 
 Sophie\, Josh\, and Scatty emerge in Paris\, the City of Lights. Home for 
 Nicholas Flamel. Only this homecoming is anything but sweet. Perenelle is 
 still locked up back in Alcatraz and Paris is teeming with enemies. Niccolo 
 Machiavelli\, immortal author and celebrated art collector\, is working for 
 Dee. He’s after them\, and time is running out for Nicholas and 
 Perenelle. For every day spent without the Book of Abraham the Mage\, they 
 age one year-their magic becoming weaker and their bodies more frail. For 
 Flamel\, the Prophecy is becoming more and more clear. It’s time for 
 Sophie to learn the second elemental magic: Fire Magic. And there’s only 
 one man who can teach it to her: Flamel’s old student\, the Comte de 
 Saint-Germain-alchemist\, magician\, and rock star. Josh and Sophie Newman 
 are the world’s only hope-if they don’t turn on each other first.
LOCATION:North Regional - Children's Programming Room\, North Regional Library (221 Milton Rd)
ORGANIZER;CN="Dominique Diggs":MAILTO:fdiggs@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Book Club
UID:LibCal-14288-15092482
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/15092482
END:VEVENT
