SUMMARY:CANCELED - Preschool STEAM Storytime: Let's Learn About Time! - CANCELED
DESCRIPTION:Hi friends! Preschool STEAM Storytime is canceled today. We 
 apologize for any inconveniences\, and we thank you for your understanding. 
 See you at the next session of Preschool STEAM Storytime!\n\nPreschoolers 
 (ages 3-5 years) and their caregivers are welcome to join Ms. Natalie for a 
 STEAM (Science\, Technology\, Engineering\, Arts\, and Mathematics) 
 storytime! On the 1st and 3rd Monday of every month\, we will explore a 
 different STEAM topic with stories\, songs\, and a hands-on 
 activity.\n\nThis week\, we will learn all about time and create our own 
 clocks using paper plates\, cardstock paper\, crayons\, markers\, and brass 
 fasteners!\n\nRegistration is required.\n\nIf you have any questions\, 
 please contact us @ 919-560-8592.
LOCATION:Southwest Regional - Children's Programming Room\, Southwest Regional Library (3605 Shannon Rd)
