SUMMARY:Homework with Friends
DESCRIPTION:Looking for a fun and supportive place to do your homework? 
 Don’t want to study alone? Need school supplies to complete that perfect 
 project?\n\nCome join us at the Durham County Main Library for Homework 
 with Friends\, a welcoming and educational program designed for students in 
 grades K - 5. Friendly volunteers from Duke University are here to help 
 with homework\, answer questions\, and provide guidance.\n\nStudents who 
 need extra support in reading or math can also sign up for one-on-one 
 tutoring through the LEAP program.\n\nSpace is limited and registration is 
 required\, so reserve your spot today!\n\n\n\na {\n    text-decoration: 
 none\;\n    color: #464feb\;\n}\ntr th\, tr td {\n    border: 1px solid 
 #e6e6e6\;\n}\ntr th {\n    background-color: #f5f5f5\;\n}\n\n\n\n¿Buscas 
 un lugar divertido y acogedor para hacer tu tarea? ¿No quieres estudiar 
 solo/a? ¿Necesitas materiales escolares para completar ese proyecto 
 perfecto?\n\n¡Ven a la Biblioteca Principal del Condado de Durham y 
 participa en Homework with Friends\, un programa educativo y acogedor 
 diseñado para estudiantes de Kínder a 5.º grado. Voluntarios amigables 
 de la Universidad de Duke estarán disponibles para ayudarte con la tarea\, 
 responder preguntas y ofrecer orientación.\n\nLos estudiantes que 
 necesiten apoyo adicional en lectura o matemáticas también pueden 
 inscribirse en tutorías individuales a través del programa LEAP.\n\nEl 
 cupo es limitado y se requiere inscripción\, ¡así que reserva tu lugar 
 hoy mismo!\n
LOCATION:MakerLab\, Main Library (300 N. Roxboro St)
ORGANIZER;CN="Maria Ramirez-Heuser":MAILTO:mrheuser@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Bilingual, Community Engagement, High & Low Sensory Stimulation, Literacy, Spanish, Tutoring
UID:LibCal-14288-15979257
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/15979257
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260302T223000Z
DTEND:20260303T003000Z
DTSTAMP:20260302T000000Z
SUMMARY:Are Your Ducks in a Row?
DESCRIPTION:Who will make your health decisions if you are unable to make 
 them yourself?\n\nNone of us want to think about it\, right? But at some 
 point in the future\, we all may face a situation where important decisions 
 must be made about our healthcare\, but we are unable to speak for 
 ourselves. Or perhaps this has happened to a loved one. Are you 
 prepared?\n\nCome to this workshop to learn how to get your ducks in a row. 
 This will be an informative workshop about advanced care planning\, 
 healthcare\, proxies\, legal paperwork\, and will include an interactive 
 exercise that will clarify your thoughts.\n\nThere will be time offered at 
 the end of the program to get paperwork and forms notarized.\n\n 
 \n\nPresenter bio:\n\nBetsy Barton\, MPH\, CT \n\nBetsy Barton is the 
 Senior Associate for Community Engagement & Learning at Transitions 
 LifeCare in Raleigh. She plans and conducts interactive education on a 
 variety of topics for clinical and community audiences. \n\nBefore coming 
 to Transitions\, she worked at the Duke Institute on Care at the End of 
 Life\, the Duke Health Inequalities Program\, and on Duke research teams 
 related to serious illness\, caregiver stress\, medical decision-making\, 
 and race-based differences regarding decision-making at the end of life. 
 \n\nShe has lived in Durham since 1978\, and received her Master of Public 
 Health degree from UNC-Chapel Hill in 1990.
LOCATION:Conference Room #3214\, Main Library (300 N. Roxboro St)
ORGANIZER;CN="Natalie Killion":MAILTO:nkillion@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Community Engagement, Health & Fitness
UID:LibCal-14288-16260120
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/16260120
END:VEVENT
