URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/16349394
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260303T230000Z
DTEND:20260304T003000Z
DTSTAMP:20260303T000000Z
SUMMARY:Nic Cage Film Discussion Group
DESCRIPTION:The man... The myth... The legend... \n\nNIC CAGE! \n\n\n\nA 
 film career that has spanned decades and genres\, blockbusters and direct 
 to video\, Nic Cage is a force unto himself. \n\nIncomparable practicing 
 his own style of method acting which he calls Nouveau shamanism he 
 transcends acting conventions. \n\nThe only actor meta enough to have 
 played himself. The only actor to have become an internet meme. The only 
 actor to have a library film discussion group devoted to him.  \n\n 
 \n\n\n\nEach month we will discuss a different film from Nic Cage’s long 
 and productive film career. \n\nFilms cover early career classics like 
 Valley Girl to later performances like Dream Scenario. Please see the film 
 schedule listed below.  \n\n \n\n\n\nSuggested reading for the discussion 
 group:   \n\nAge of Cage: Four Decades of Hollywood Through One Singular 
 Career by Keith Phipps  \n\nAvailable here: Age of Cage   \n\n \n\nNational 
 Treasure: Nicolas Cage by Lindsay Gibb (ISBN-13: ‎978-1770412361)  
 \n\nAvailable as an e-book here: National Treasure \n\nAvailable via an 
 Interlibrary Loan request here: InterLibrary Loan Request   \n\nHow Coppola 
 Became Cage by Zach Schonfeld (ISBN-13 : 978-0197556375)\n\nAvailable as an 
 e-audio book here: How Coppola Became Cage\n\nAvailable via an Interlibrary 
 Loan request here: InterLibrary Loan Request   \n\n \n\n\n\nSome films can 
 be found in the library catalog here: Durham County Library Online Catalog 
 \n\n \n\n\n\nDidn’t watch the film? That’s ok! Feel free to join as Nic 
 Cage transcends discussions about specific films! \n\n \n\nRefreshments 
 will be served however please bring your own covered beverage.  \n\n 
 \n\nFirst Tuesday of the month\, excluding April\, starting at 6 pm in the 
 Children's Programming Room on the second floor of the Durham County Main 
 Library located at 300 North Roxboro Street.  \n\n*January's Discussion 
 Group will be in the Main Library Auditorium \n\nParking is available in 
 the library parking lot or the North Queen Street Garage located at 115 
 North Queen Street which is located directly across the street from the 
 library behind the apartments. Parking in the garage is free. Please bring 
 your parking ticket to a service point for validation.  \n\nRegistration is 
 appreciated but not required. Register to receive email reminders.  \n\n 
 \n\n\n\nSchedule of films for 2026: \n\nJanuary 6 – Vampire’s Kiss 
 \n\nFebruary 3 – Valley Girl \n\nMarch 3 – Wild At Heart \n\nApril – 
 No discussion group \n\nMay 5 – Raising Arizona \n\nJune 2 – Dream 
 Scenario \n\nJuly 7 – Con Air \n\nAugust 4 – Leaving Las Vegas 
 \n\nSeptember 1 – Gone in 60 Seconds  \n\nOctober 6 – Willy’s 
 Wonderland \n\nNovember 3 – The Rock \n\nDecember 1 – Matchstick Men  
 \n\n \n\nQuestions? Contact mkoslofsky@dconc.gov \n\n \n\n\n\nPhoto credit: 
 Georges Biard \n
LOCATION:Main Children's Programming Room\, Main Library (300 N. Roxboro St)
ORGANIZER;CN="Megan Koslofsky":MAILTO:mkoslofsky@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Durham, Movie, Social
UID:LibCal-14288-15314192
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/15314192
END:VEVENT
