SUMMARY:ACT or SAT for Your Student?
DESCRIPTION:APlus Test Prep is coming to North Regional to provide free 
 sessions geared towards Teens and their families. The ACT OR SAT FOR YOUR 
 STUDENT is designed to help teens decide which test to take since students 
 don't have to take both. \n\nDuring this class\, students will evaluate 
 their testing style\; complete a series of timed reading\, math\, & English 
 questions from the ACT & SAT\; anticipate their performance on each test\; 
 and participate in a Q&A with their parents.\n\nAt the end of this 
 seminar\, students will have a clearer sense of which test they should take 
 as they prepare for college admissions.\n\nRegistration is required.  
 Contact Dominique Diggs at fdiggs@dconc.gov with any questions or 
 concerns.\n\nYou can learn more about APlus Test Prep by visiting their 
 website: aplushigherscores.com
LOCATION:North Regional - Children's Programming Room\, North Regional Library (221 Milton Rd)
ORGANIZER;CN="Dominique Diggs":MAILTO:fdiggs@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:
