BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260304T223000Z
DTEND:20260305T003000Z
DTSTAMP:20260304T000000Z
SUMMARY:SCORE presents: Welcome to Entrepreneurship
DESCRIPTION:You MUST register via SCORE's registration link: Welcome To 
 Entrepreneurship | SCORE\n\nDuring this two hour in-person session you will 
 learn about:\n\n\n	Personal characteristics of an Entrepreneur\n	Legal 
 entities—LLC vs. Sole Proprietorship \n	Federal ID Number\n	Business 
 Feasibility Analysis\n	Capital—Equity vs. Debt\n	Basic Bookkeeping Made 
 Easy\n	Business Modeling\n	Insurance\n	Taxes—Filing requirements for 
 Federal and State\n\n\nLastly\, you will be introduced to SCORE and the 
 invaluable work that their Mentors provide to new start-ups.\n\nThe class 
 will be presented by Mr. Fred Lorber\, a certified SCORE mentor and class 
 instructor.\n\nMr. Lorber is a seasoned entrepreneur\, business development 
 expert\, and accomplished speaker with over three decades of experience in 
 sales\, strategic planning\, and customer relationship 
 management.\n\nLorber’s areas of expertise include new business 
 development\, strategic planning\, B2B sales\, and negotiation\, all honed 
 through a diverse career that spans industries such as e-commerce\, website 
 development\, hospitality\, and retail. Mr. Lorber has consistently 
 delivered results\, including growing businesses from start-up to 
 profitability\, improving customer engagement metrics\, and training teams 
 to achieve operational excellence.
LOCATION:Conference Room #3214\, Main Library (300 N. Roxboro St)
ORGANIZER;CN="Jana Bradley":MAILTO:jbradley@dconc.gov
CATEGORIES:Business, Career Development, Low Sensory Stimulation
UID:LibCal-14288-15430214
URL:https://durhamcountylibrary.libcal.com/event/15430214
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
